<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Norway 1-0 in Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Tiffeny Milbrett scored a lone goal
to pace the United States for a 1-0 victory over Norway in the
opening game of the German Football Federation (DFB) Jubilee
tournament in Osnabrueck, Germany Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Milbrett took a pass about 40 yards from the goal, raced around
a defender and scored from 12 yards out, helping the United States
for two consecutive wins against Norway after losing twice in
February.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Norway still leads the United States 13-12 in the series
with one tie, and the two teams will meet on September 15 at
Melbourne, Australia in the first round of the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The game also marked the 200th cap for both Mia Hamm and
Kristine Lilly.
</P>
<P>
Norway turned up the pressure during the last 15 minutes
against the American women who intended on protecting their lead,
with midfielder Hege Riise in particular, as she became one of the
best midfielders in the world.
</P>
<P>
In another game, China defeated Germany 3-1 and will face the
United States on Wednesday in Gottingen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
