<HEADLINE> India, Oman to Set Up Strategic Consultative Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This was agreed at a meeting between visiting Foreign Minister
of Oman Yusuf Din Alawi Bin Abdullah, who arrived here Sunday on a
three-day official visit, and External Affairs Minister of India
Jaswant Singh.
</P>
<P>
Both sides decided to expedite implementation of the 1.1
billion U.S. dollars Indo-Oman Fertilizer project in Oman and the
joint venture Oil Refinery project in Madhya Pradesh in Central
India.
</P>
<P>
The Omani minister called on Prime Minister Atal Bihari
Vajpayee and highlighted the immense potential for further
enhancing economic cooperation in diversified fields.
</P>
<P>
A foreign office spokesman said that India attached high
importance to relations with Oman, which is strategically located.
Indians numbering over 340,000 in Oman constitute the largest
expatriate group in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
