<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Black Boxes of Ill-Fated Indian Plane Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Civil Aviation Secretary A.H. Jung said the Cockpit Voice
Recorder (CVR) and Voice Data Recorder (VDR) would provide crucial
data on the cause of the crash of the ill-fated Alliance Air plane.
</P>
<P>
Asked how long it would take to decode these two black boxes,
he said it could probably take a week.
</P>
<P>
The latest official figures said that 55 people were killed in
the air crash. While 51 passengers including the crew were killed
on the spot, four people on the ground died in the house collapse.
However, seven passengers had a miraculous escape.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the notification for setting up of the Court of
Inquiry would be issued within a day or two. 
</P>
</TEXT>
