<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Serviceman Killed in Multinational War Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A Ukrainian serviceman was killed
during the sixth multinational exercise "Peace Shield-2000" at
Ukraine's Yavoriv training range last Sunday, the Ukrainian
Defense Ministry's press-service told reporters Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the press-service, Junior Sergeant Volodymyr
Dutchak, commander of a mechanized unit of the 7 mechanized
regiment, was run over by an armored troop-carrier, when escorting
a humanitarian cargo.
</P>
<P>
This was the first death reported from the Peace Shield
exercises, which have been held for five times in the past years
without any casualties.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,600 servicemen from 21 countries -- Greece, Denmark,
Italy, Canada, Germany, Norway, Poland, the U.S.A, Turkey, Finland,
Sweden, Britain, Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Belarus, Georgia,
Kazakhstan, Ukraine, Moldova and Estonia -- are taking part in the
nine-day war game, which is due to close on July 22.
</P>
<P>
Portugal, Switzerland, France, Lithuania and Hungary are also
attending the military exercise as observers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
