<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 16 Injured in Road Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and 16 others
injured in Egypt on Tuesday in a road accident involving a lorry
and two mini-buses.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place on the road linking Cairo and Assiut,
330 kilometers south of the capital, when a front tire of the lorry
punctured, said a statement issued by the Ministry of Interior.
</P>
<P>
The lorry veered and crashed head-on into a mini-bus, and
another following immediately ran into the wrecked vehicles, the
state-run MENA news agency reported, quoting the statement.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the lorry, 28, was killed in the incident, the
statement said. But no details were given to the identities of the
other eight who perished in the accident.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt, blamed on violation of
traffic rules and reckless driving, and often cause major loss of
lives as vehicles are mostly crammed. In the most recent accident,
19 people were killed and 15 others injured on Monday when a mini-
bus ran head-on into a car in southern Minya Governorate. 
</P>
