<HEADLINE> European Envoy Hails Rwanda's Democratization Process. . </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A visiting official from the
European Union (EU) said in Rwandan capital Tuesday that Rwanda
has made some progress in its democratization process, according
to a report by Rwanda News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"We recognize a change in the democratization process in Rwanda
manifested in the local government general elections held last
year, where people had to line-up behind candidates of their own
choice and this year's elections of the county chiefs where the
secret ballot shall be employed," EU's special representative to
the Great Lakes region Aldo Ayello told a press conference held
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ayello said, "For us, the democratization process is not a '
recipe' that we are trying to sell to our African friends. Our
idea is that democracy in Africa should follow their history,
culture, traditional, economical and social situation and even
ethnic composition of each country."
</P>
<P>
The EU envoy highlighted the pillars of democracy that the EU
is committed to, which include the right of the people to choose
leaders through general elections, the separation of judiciary,
legislative and executive powers and a protecting system of human
rights and fundamental freedom.
</P>
<P>
The envoy's visit to Rwanda is aimed at evaluating the
democratization process in Rwanda, the performance of its Justice
sector and the peaceful resolution of the conflict in the
Democratic Republic of the Congo,
</P>
<P>
He said the EU strongly believed that, the Lusaka Agreement is
the only base agreed upon by all parties and it must be
implemented as a result. 
</P>
