<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Opposition Protests Against High Living Cost </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 18 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lanka's main opposition United
National Party (UNP) Tuesday held here a mammoth protest march
against the rising cost of living.
</P>
<P>
An estimated crowd of over 10,000 people gathered near one of
Colombo's main railway stations creating a massive traffic block.
</P>
<P>
A party spokesman said that many farmers had arrived from
outstations to vent their anger against the rising cost of living
due to the recent depreciation of the country's currency rupee and
the price hike of gas, diesel, electricity and telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the protesting crowd, the UNP Leader Ranil
Wickremesinghe pledged that if elected to power his government
will bring the rising cost of living down and ease the burden on
the poor masses.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan President Kumaratunga has said that the 11th
Parliament elections will be held during the first week of
November after the current parliament is dissolved on August 24.
</P>
