<HEADLINE> Haas Rallies to Beat Czech Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Host favourite Tommy Haas came
from a six match points to defeat Czech qualifier David Miketa 3-6,
7-5, 6-2 on Tuesday to reach the second round of the Stuttgart
Open, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old German, seeded sixth in the claycourt event,
lost the first set and was 5-4 down in the second but the
unheralded Miketa then wasted his chances to seal the match before
collapsing in the decisive set.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia's Dominik Hrbaty, the eighth seed, was the first
seeded player to bow out of the tournament, beaten 6-3, 7-5 by
Czech Jiri Novak.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's Andrei Medvedev crushed Bernd Karbacher 6-3, 6-2 in
the 32-year-old German's last singles match on the professional
circuit.
</P>
<P>
"It's not easy but it's time," said Karbacher, announcing his
retirement.
</P>
<P>
Karbacher reached a career-high 22nd in the world rankings in
1995. But he was then hampered by a string of knee injuries and
fell to a modest 246th in the ATP Champions' Race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
