<HEADLINE> South Africa to Host SADC Cultural Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of Southern
African Development Community countries will meet for eight days
from Wednesday to discuss co-operation on cultural issues, South
African Deputy Arts and Culture Minister Brigitte Mabandla said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mabandla said she hoped SADC ministers and officials would
look at arts and culture as means to unify the region, although
member states had cooperated in this field in the past.
</P>
<P>
"We, as South Africans, cannot develop in isolation," she said.
</P>
<P>
The conference -- dubbed Kopano, which means "gathering" in
Sotho -- would cost about 1 million rand (147,000 US dollars), she
said.
</P>
<P>
It will also attract international speakers from outside the
SADC Region, she said.
</P>
<P>
The conference will take place on a game farm, north of South
African capital Pretoria from July 19 to July 26. 
</P>
