<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's ruling party,
The African National Congress (ANC), on Tuesday celebrated former
president Nelson Mandela's 82nd birthday, saying it would continue
to benefit from Mandela's "wisdom and lofty leadership for many
more years to come".
</P>
<P>
ANC spokesman Nat Serache said Mandela had to remember that
the country was celebrating his birthday with him and proudly
remembered the sacrifices he had made over the years to enable it
to become the envy of the world.
</P>
