<HEADLINE> France Wins Big Trade Surplus in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS,July 18(Xinhua) -- France won 12.3 billion francs (1.8
billion U.S. dollars) of trade surplus in May, mainly because of
the sale of a record number of Airbus planes and good performance
of its civilian industry.
</P>
<P>
The French Customs said on Tuesday that the surplus in May is
eight times as high as that in April, which saw a 1.554 billion
franc (229 million U.S. dollars) surplus.
</P>
<P>
France's overall trade surplus in the first five months this
year amounted to 27.564 billion francs (4 billion U.S. dollars),
lower than the same period last year, which registered a 44.7
billion franc (6.57 billion U.S. dollars) surplus.
</P>
<P>
The lowering of the trade surplus is partly caused by the
rising of oil prices in world markets.
</P>
<P>
France sold 18 Airbus passenger planes, a steam ship and
several satellites in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
