<HEADLINE> Chad Denies Fall of Garrison to Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chad denied on Tuesday the fall of a
strategic garrison in the northern desert to the rebel force of
Movement for Democracy and Justice in Chad (MDJC), according to a
report by Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The government forces are still controlling the garrison of
Bardai and fighting is continuing around it, the agency quoted the
Chadian government as saying in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The attackers are in the process of pulling out from the area
after meeting strong resistance from government forces, the
communique said.
</P>
<P>
AFP also quoted an anonymous source of the Chadian government
as saying that the MDJC tried to catch the garrison in order to
use it as an air support base to receive logistics from a third
country.
</P>
<P>
The MDJC, which has been harassing government forces in the
northern desert region of Tibesti since October 1998, said on
Tuesday that it had taken the garrison of Bardai, killing 240
government soldiers and wounding hundreds of others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
