<HEADLINE> Virenque Wins 16th Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Richard Virenque won the
16th stage of the Tour de France on Tuesday after rival Roberto
Heras crashed in the final two kilometers.
</P>
<P>
German Jan Ullrich was second and Spain's Heras third in the
196.5-kilometres leg from Courchevel to Morzine.
</P>
<P>
American Lance Armstrong retained the overall lead although he
struggled up the final Col de Joux-Plane and finished in eighth
place.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong is now 5 minutes, 37 seconds ahead of second-placed
Ullrich in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Virenque, who rides for Polti, finished the route in five
hours, 32 minutes, 20 seconds after a brave climb up the final
mountain of the race.
</P>
<P>
He was battling for first place with Heras when the Spanish
rider crashed into barriers going round a bend.  
</P>
