<HEADLINE> Second Yangtze Flood Crest Passing Crucial River Section </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The second Yangtze River flood crest
this summer today arrived at the meandering Jingjiang section,
which is considered the most crucial section on the river for anti-
flood precautions.
</P>
<P>
The crest passing the Shashi Hydrometeorological Station in
central China's Hubei Province at 53,000 cu m per second this
morning, surpassing the danger line by 0.01 m. This is the first
time this summer that the flood has risen over the mark, according
to the station's records.
</P>
<P>
The second crest was formed by the gathering of mammoth water
flows from the upper reaches of the Yangtze and its tributaries,
which have received large amounts of rainfall, with flooding in
the Three Gorges area.
</P>
<P>
No danger spots have been reported at press time. All provinces
along the lower reaches are on high anti-flood alert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
