<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Branches of CCB Provide New Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Shanghai, China's
biggest industrial and commercial center, may make the down
payments for their new houses now with loans offered by the local
branch of the China Construction Bank (CCB).
</P>
<P>
Since they can apply for the loan with their old houses and
the new houses they will buy as the mortgage, they don't have to
afford the payment immediately, which usually accounts for over 20
percent of the cost of a new house and is a great burden for most
people.
</P>
<P>
Insiders pointed out that the measure has greatly eased the
pressure on those citizens who are not rich but hope to improve
their living conditions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, CCB's branch in Wenzhou City in east China's
Zhejiang Province, offers a similar services, making it possible
for individuals to subscribe to newspapers, pay utility bills, and
buy cars and houses, as well as pay children's tuition fees,
through the local outlets of the bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
