<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICBC Cooperates with City Commercial Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Ten branches and offices of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) today signed agency
contracts with 10 city commercial banks on payment settlement
businesses.
</P>
<P>
According to the contracts, the 10 city commercial banks will
entrust the ICBC to do its payment settlement businesses, marking
the beginning for the two sides to establish a standardized and
legalized cooperative relationship.
</P>
<P>
China's city commercial banks have been developing rapidly over
the past several years amid the country's reinforced financial
system reforms, and have contributed significantly to China's
economic construction.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the ICBC, China's largest commercial bank, has unique
advantages in capital strength, number of business offices,
business species, and client bases among domestic commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
Based on its nationwide business network, the ICBC has been
providing settlement services for many large enterprises and
financial institutions. 
</P>
