<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine has written a letter to his Russian counterpart Igor
Ivanov to explain the seizure of the Russian yacht "Sedov" last
week at the French port of Brest.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry assistant spokesman Francois Rivasseau
said on Tuesday that the Foreign Ministry is in constant contact
with the Russian embassy in Paris to "examine the best ways to
solve this problem."
</P>
<P>
French judicial authorities seized "Sedov" last Thursday after
the yacht arrived at the invitation of the annual Brest
international yachts rally.
</P>
<P>
The move was made at the request of the Geneva-based import-
export company Noga which accuses the Russian government of
refusing to pay it 1.4 billion U.S. dollars for the food it sold
to Russia in 1992.
</P>
<P>
"Sedov," a 117-meter, four-mast white yacht with 176 people on
board, is the vedette of the Russian fleet belonging to the
Murmansk Military Technology University.
</P>
<P>
Russia has warned France of serious consequences if it does not
release the yacht. 
</P>
