<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Russia to Strengthen Anti-crime Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Russia will strengthen
cooperation in curbing cross-border crimes such as arms smuggling,
drug trafficking and illegal migration, said a joint statement
signed here Tuesday by their interior ministers.
</P>
<P>
Emerging from a working meeting with his Russian counterpart,
Vladimir Rushailo, Ukrainian Interior Minister Yury Kravchenko
told reporters that the two countries' law-enforcement
departments have already done dozens of joint operations against
such cross-border crimes, common problems facing them.
</P>
