<HEADLINE> Summer Camp for Cross-Straits Teenagers Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A seven-day summer camp for
teenagers from both sides of the Taiwan Straits opened near this
western China metropolis today.
</P>
<P>
The camp, aimed at promoting exchanges among teenagers from
Taiwan and the Chinese mainland, is hosting nearly 90 teenagers,
over 50 of them from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
A second-year college student from Taiwan University said the
modernization in Chongqing was beyond his imagination, and he is
eager to know more about the Chinese mainland during the camp.
</P>
<P>
As part of the camp activities, scholars will be invited to
give lectures on the history, culture and customs of the Three
Gorges area for the Taiwanese young people's better understanding
of the development of civilization along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The campers will visit the Three Gorges, and later go to Wuhan,
in central China's Hubei Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
