<HEADLINE> Treasuries Up at Tuesday Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasuries picked up
broadly today but the trade kept thin with a trading value of 1.45
billion yuan, 47 million more than yesterday.
</P>
<P>
009908, a 3.30 percent bond due 2009, edged up 0.24 percent to
close at 101.90 yuan with an expanded trading volume, pressing the
yield down 0.04 percentage points to 3.42 percentage points,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
000696 (11.83 percent, due 2006) picked up 0.15 percent to
become the second biggest gainer, followed by Bond 010004 with a
rise of 0.12 percent, Bond 009908 with 0.06 percent, Bond 009704
with 0.04 percent, and Bond 009905 with 0.02 percent.
</P>
<P>
National Bureau of Statistics figures show that China's
Consumer Price Index (CPI) edged up 0.1 percent in the first half
of this year, a sign of improvement following continuous falls in
the past two years. But little concern among investors is seen on
potential inflation.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts said the market sentiment is high for stocks
and many investors are looking forward to 2000 points on the
Shanghai Stock Composite Index, leaving China's T-bond trade
sluggish. 
