<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WFP Launches Major Relief Operation for Drought-hit Afghans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations World Food
Program (WFP) Tuesday announced a major relief operation to help
up to 1.6 million famine-threatened people survive the worst
drought in Afghanistan in over 30 years.
</P>
<P>
Under this new emergency operation, WFP will bring about 120,
000 metric tons of food into Afghanistan at a cost of 55.4 million
U.S. dollars over the coming 12 months.
</P>
<P>
WFP estimates that between 8 to 12 million Afghans will be
affected by the drought and between 3 to 4 million severely
affected.
</P>
<P>
The extremely low level of precipitation in the first half of
2000 has destroyed almost all the rain-fed crops in the country
and decimated the livestock. The next chance for a normal crop
will not be until May 2001, it said.
</P>
<P>
The cereal deficit for Afghanistan in 2000/2001 is expected to
be as high as 2.3 million tons, more than double that of the
previous year, said Mike Sackett, WFP Afghanistan Country Director.
</P>
<P>
The director further observed that the effects of the drought
are seriously aggravated by the ongoing civil war and an economy
which in many areas is in a state of collapse.
</P>
<P>
Afghanistan, a country in war for the last 21 years, needs
about 4.1 million tons of cereals a year to meet domestic
consumption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Euro Zone Annual Inflation Up to 2.4 Perent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Euro zone annual inflation rate
rose from 1.9 percent to 2.4 percent between May and June, the
fastest year-on-year change since March 1996, European Union's
statistical office, Eurostat, said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A year earlier the inflation rate was 0.9 percent. Meanwhile,
annual inflation rate in the 15-nation European Union -- 11-
country euro zone plus Britain, Greece, Sweden and Denmark -- rose
from 1.7 percent in May to 2.1 percent in June. The EU's rate was
1.0 percent in June 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to the Eurostat, the highest annual inflation rates
among EU member states were in Ireland (5.4 percent), Luxembourg (
4.4 percent), and Spain (3.5 percent), while the lowest rates were
in Britain (0.8 percent), Sweden (1.4 percent) and France (1.9
percent).
</P>
<P>
Compared with May 2000, the year-on-year inflation rose in 14
EU member states and fell in Greece. Compared to that of June 1999,
the biggest relative rises were in Austria (0.2 percent to 2.4
percent), France (0.3 percent to 1.9 percent) and Germany (0.4
percent to 2.0 percent).
</P>
<P>
The only relative fall was in Britain (1.4 percent to 0.8
percent).
</P>
<P>
The Eurostat said the lowest 12-month averages up to June were
in Sweden and Britain (both 1.0 percent), and France (1.2 percent).
The highest were in Ireland (3.9 percent), Spain (2.8 percent),
and Denmark (2.7 percent).
</P>
<P>
The euro zone countries are Belgium, Germany, Spain, France,
Ireland Italy, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Austria, Portugal and
Finland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
