<HEADLINE> Manila to Host World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- With seven of eight teams competing
in the Sydney Games, the World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix in
Manila next month will be a virtual Olympic preview, accorting to
organizers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We will have seven of eight top volleyball-playing nations
which have qualified for the Sydney Olympics. This makes the World
Women's Volleyball Grand Prix a preview of the Olympics," Benny
Gopez, chairman of the Philippine Amateur Volleyball Association,
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Top-ranked and defending champion Russia heads the cast of the
tournament where the country will stage one preliminary leg on
August 18-20. The semifinals and finals will be held on August 24-
27. All matches are staged in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Aside from Russia, Italy, Korea and Brazil will also vie in the
Manila preliminary leg, after which they will be joined by the
United States, China, Cuba and Japan in the final stage.
</P>
<P>
Only Japan, out of the eight teams, missed earning a ticket to
the Sydney Summer Games in September.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines hosted one preliminary leg of last year's World
Women's Volleyball Grand Prix. 
</P>
</TEXT>
