<HEADLINE> Kuerten Heads HK Salem Open Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- French open champion Gustavo
Kuerten of Brazil will make his debut at the 370,000 U.S. dollar
Hong Kong Salem Tennis Open in October.
</P>
<P>
It was announced here on Tuesday by the Hong Kong Tennis
Association.
</P>
<P>
Joining the Brazilian are this year's Winbledon finalist
Patrick Rafter of Australia and Nicolas Kiefer, Germany's number
one and promising star.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Salem Tennis Open is Hong Kong's only ATP Tour event
and will take place from October 2nd to 8th.
</P>
<P>
According the organizer, the 32-draw tournament will attract a
powerhouse field of stars because the open is to be staged back-to-
back with the Sydney Olympics. Coupled with the fact, no other
tournament in the world will be held during the Salem Open week.
</P>
