<HEADLINE> Major Gas Discovery in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China has discovered some ten gas-
bearing structures in the Southwest China Petroleum Gas Field
since the beginning of this year, with the drilling success rate
hitting 75.86 percent, according to today's China Petrochemical
News.
</P>
<P>
The discovery signals a huge potential for gas development in
southwest China, the paper said, adding that gas reserves in the
ten structures are expected to hit over 50 billion cu m.
</P>
<P>
Two gas wells have already been sunk in Luojiazhai, the most
important one of the ten gas-bearing structures, and rich gas
flows have been found which were tested at 433,000 cu m and 632,
000 cu m daily, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Experts expect the gas reserves contained in the two wells to
total around 15 billion cu m, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
