<HEADLINE> Qinghai Oilfield Produces More Crude Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Qinghai Oilfield in northwest
China aims to turn out two million tons of crude oil and 450
million cu m of natural gas by the end of this year, according to
today's China Petroleum News.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that by the end of June the oilfield had turned
out 984,000 tons of crude oil and 179 million cu m of gas, up 6.4
percent and 4.4 percent, respectively, over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
By the latter half of June, the daily crude oil output of the
oilfield had topped 5,520 tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
