<HEADLINE> Shanghai A Share Up At Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Total trading value was 10.96 billion yuan (about 1.32 billion
U.S. dollars), 29.4 percent less than Monday's 15.54 billion yuan,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai composite index closed strongly at 1993.99 points,
which may be a prelude for 2,000 points. But the turnover was not
extended, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech and some ST stocks performed actively. Two new A
shares with high-tech concept will be listed tomorrow, so the high-
tech shares may become market leaders tomorrow to lead the index
to the 2000-point target.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Tyre and Rubber Co., Ltd.(600623.SS) was the top
gainer today with its price up 10.02 percent to its ceiling of 14.
17 yuan, as the company is likely to sign a 300-million-U.S.-
dollar agreement with Michelin &AMP; Cie.SCA, Europe's No.1 tyre maker,
by the end of July.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Jiufa edible Fungus Co.,Ltd.(600180.SS) was the
biggest loser. Its price shed 5.93 percent to 20.62 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the market is likely to try 2,
000 points tomorrow. 
</P>
