<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Up At Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
rose 0.09 points, or 0.16 percent, to 58.40 at the close on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 14.01 million U.S. dollars (116.28 million yuan),
a slight change from Monday's 14.23 million, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market staged a quiet advance today as optimistic
expectations for corporate earnings boosted the index while some
profit taking took place. But buyers moved in quickly.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outpaced advancing shares by 19 to 17, with 18
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tire &AMP; Rubber (900909.SS) soared 10.10 percent to 0.218 U.S.
dollars. The company may be financially boosted and have its debts
loaded off from a confirmed 300-million U.S.-dollar deal with
Michelin group, Europe's No.1 tire maker, by the end of July. Also
on the winners' list was Matsuoka (900941.SS) which rose 3.28
percent to 0.566 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sewing Machine (900924.SS) slipped 2.54 percent to 0.230 U.S.
dollars, while Eastern Commus (900941.SS) fell 2.09 percent to 0.
842 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predicted that the market will continue to trade to
the upside as high expectations for earnings and a strong economic
growth are expected to positively impact the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
