<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Chilean Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said here
today that China, as a founding member of the Asia-Pacific
Parliamentary Forum (APPF), attaches importance to its role in the
region and has been an active participant in the organization.
</P>
<P>
Li said this when meeting this afternoon with Mario Rios,
visiting vice-president of the Senate of the National Congress of
Chile. Chile will host the APPF annual session in January 2001.
</P>
<P>
As the most influential parliamentary organization in the Asia-
Pacific region, the APPF has emerged as an important forum for
parliamentarians from all the countries in the region to exchange
views upon various issues, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Chile appreciates China's role in the APPF, and considers the
participation of China in the coming session very important, Rios
said.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed satisfaction with the progress of China's
relations over the past 30 years with Chile, the first country in
South America to establish diplomatic ties with China.
</P>
<P>
China appreciates the adherence of the Chilean government and
National Congress to the One-China policy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Both sides also expressed their wishes to further enhance
exchanges between the two parliaments and promote bilateral
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
