<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Arts Website Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Federation of Literary
and Art Circles (CFLAC) today kicked off its official website for
spreading news of the state's artists and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
The website, chinabao.com, which is jointly promoted by the
CFLAC and Beijing Telecom, covers literature, performing arts,
visual arts and audio arts.
</P>
<P>
At the website's opening ceremony, Zhao Zhihong, vice-chairman
of the CFLAC, said that the units have tried to use advanced
technologies in popularizing traditional Chinese culture and arts.
</P>
<P>
The website also features on-line exhibitions, purchase,
auction, education and a database of well-known Chinese artists.
</P>
<P>
Preparing to construct the website which now contains over 2,
000 pages, the CFLAC on March 23 specially established an
editorial body, consisting of officials and experts in cultural
circles.
</P>
<P>
In the second phase of its development, the website is
scheduled to provide Internet surfers with further editions in
English and Japanese, as well as in the original complex form of
Chinese characters which is familiar to Chinese abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
