<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Teachers' Inventions Exhibited in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China's first national exhibition
on teaching-aid inventions opened here today, with the presence of
teachers from primary and middle schools across China.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 300 items of teaching tools invented or improved by
Chinese teachers in recent years will be on display during the
three-day show.
</P>
<P>
The exhibited items cover subjects such as Chinese language and
literature, mathematics, physics, chemistry, biology, geography
and astronomy.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade, the Chinese government has begun to shift
emphasis from an education based entirely on taking examinations
to focusing on other aspects of student performance in schools.
</P>
<P>
The show, first of its kind in China and supported by the
Ministry of Education and China Association for Science and
Technology, aims to promote enthusiasm for invention among
teachers nationwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
