<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Technical Guideline on Urban Garbage Disposal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China today issued a 10-page
technical guideline on urban garbage disposal, in a bid to tackle
the pollution caused by the country's growing mountains of
domestic garbage.
</P>
<P>
Yang Luyu, director of the Department of Urban Construction
under the Ministry of Construction, said the policy was also
designed to improve garbage disposal technology and reduce the
waste of resources through the adoption of proper disposal
technology.
</P>
<P>
The policy calls for measures to reduce the amount of garbage
discharged in urban areas, including discouraging the practice of
excessive packaging, and promoting clean vegetables and clean fuel
for urban residents.
</P>
<P>
According to the policy, local governments are encouraged to
choose the right garbage disposal technology and equipment that
best suits local conditions.
</P>
<P>
It also encourages diversified investment in garbage disposal
facilities.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 114 million tons of domestic garbage collected last
year in the country's 668 cities was dumped in land-fill areas,
which occupy a lot of land and pollute the environment, the
director said.
</P>
<P>
Urban garbage, which has been growing at seven percent on
average each year during the past decade and more, will pose a
great threat to the country's environment unless the disposal
methods are improved, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
