<HEADLINE> Tests to Improve Quality of China's Local Police Chiefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Directors of the public security
bureaus at the county and city level in China are expected to
attend nationwide assessment tests which will check their
professional capabilities and achievements, according to a senior
official from the Ministry of Public Security here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun Mingshan, deputy head of the ministry's political
department, revealed this at a national tele-conference this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said that the practice, which was initiated in 1995, "aims
to improve the overall quality of local police chiefs and
encourage a merit certification system."
</P>
<P>
Sun urged that more attention be paid to the work, saying that
the departments concerned should take this opportunity to
encourage local police chiefs to study hard and to combine the
test results with the appointments and dismissals of police chiefs.
</P>
</TEXT>
