<HEADLINE> Chirac Leaves for Japan to Attend G-8 Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
left here on Tuesday for Japan to attend the Japan-European Union
(EU) summit on Wednesday and the Group of Eight summit in Okinawa
later this week, announced the Elysee presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by his wife, Bernadette Chirac, the French
president is due to meet on Wednesday with Japanese Prime Minister
Yoshiro Mori before making a private visit to the Japanese
economic zone of Chubu on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The president of the European Commission, Romano Prodi, and the
secretary general of the European Council, Javier Solana, will
also participate in the summit meeting between Chirac and Mori.
</P>
<P>
France resumed the six-month rotating EU presidency this month.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is due to attend the summit of the Group of Seven most
industrialized countries in Okinawa on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be turned into the Group of Eight summit
Friday evening when Russian President Vladimir Putin joins the
leaders of the seven countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
