<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Hosts Int'l Anthropology Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 180 people are gathering
in Xiamen, the main port city in east China's Fujian Province, to
attend an international anthropology conference which opened today.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day meeting, delegates will discuss how human
beings can solve problems in environment, resources and population
arising from the rapid social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Anthropologists and sociologists from the United States,
Britain, France, Spain, Canada, Japan, as well Australia and the
Netherlands are participating in the meeting, which is themed
Human Survival and Development in the 21st Century.
</P>
<P>
The academic meeting is hosted by the Xiamen Federation of
Social Sciences, Xiamen University, and several anthropology
institutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
