<HEADLINE> Profit Taking Dampens Hang Seng Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks sank Tuesday on
profit taking across the board, with the benchmark Hang Seng Index
plunging 2.21 percent, or 393.95 points, to close at 17,440.83.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was a modest 10.193 billion Hong Kong dollars (1.307
billion U.S. dollars), compared with Monday's 11.833 billion Hong
Kong dollars (1.517 billion U.S. dollars), amid investors' waiting
for the release of the U.S. consumer price index for June, due at
1330 GMT, and congressional testimony by Alan Greenspan on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All the four sub-indexes of the HSI dived, with Finance,
Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry down 2.06 percent, 0.
77 percent, 1.95 percent and 2.46 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Bucking the market trend was Legend Holdings which continued to
draw buyers on news it is to be added to the Hang Seng Index next
month.
</P>
<P>
The computer maker of the Chinese mainland soared 3.68 percent
to 8.45 Hong Kong dollars, propping up the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index lost 2.10 percent, while
the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index gained 0.12 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks opened Tuesday's morning session 68.32 points,
or 0.38 percent, lower at 17,766.46 points and closed the morning
session 277.31 points, or 1.55 percent lower at 17,557.47 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
