<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economy on Steady Rise (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's summer grain output will decrease 11 billion kilograms
or by 9.3 percent compared with that of last year. But the added
value of the agricultural sector increased by 1.5 percent year-on-
year to reach 450 billion yuan in the period.
</P>
<P>
For the first half year, retail volume totaled 1,624.8 billion
yuan, up 10.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Fixed assets investment grew 11 percent to reach 1,017.6
billion yuan in the first half this year.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign trade kept an upbeat growth momentum in the
first half of this year, with exports surging by 38.3 percent to
114.5 billion U.S. dollars, according to NBS.
</P>
<P>
Imports for the January-June period stood at 102.1 billion U.S.
dollars, up 36.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Total trade surplus amounted to 12.4 billion U.S. dollars, 4.4
billion more than the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign exchange reserves reached 158 billion U.S. dollars by
the end of May this year, 3.3 billion U.S. dollars more than at
the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
As the economy continued to grow at a fast pace, China's
industrial enterprises further improved their performance in the
first five months this year. These enterprises sold 96.8 percent
of the products manufactured in the six months, with the sales
ratio growing by 1.15 percentage points from that a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Consumer Price Index (CPI) edged up 0.1 percent in the
first half of this year, a sign of improvement following
continuous falls in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The Retail Price Index (RPI) dropped by 1.9 percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The disposable income of urban residents averaged 3,208 yuan (
about 386.5 U.S. dollars), a rise of 8.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Rural residents' cash income averaged 1,013 yuan (about 122 U.S.
dollars) during the same period, up 1.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economy on Steady Rise (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China's gross domestic product (
GDP) grew 8.2 percent year-on-year to reach 3,949.1 billion yuan
in the first half of this year, the National Bureau of Statistics
(NBS) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
NBS spokesman Ye Zhen said at a press conference held by the
Information Office under the State Council that the economic
growth for the whole year will be "certainly" higher than the
seven percent target set at the beginning of this year, and also
higher than last year's 7.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
He said that the economy was better than expected over the
first half of the year. The economy has reversed a slowing trend
and shown a forward momentum.
</P>
<P>
This showed that China's economy has already shrugged off the
negative impact of the Asian financial crisis and the macro-
economic control measures have yielded positive results, according
to Ye.
</P>
<P>
He said that an important opportunity for the economy to bounce
back has emerged.
</P>
<P>
NBS figures indicate that China's secondary industry reported a
total output value of 2,136.5 billion yuan for the first half this
year, an increase of 9.7 percent from the same period last year.
Industrial output was 1,900.5 billion yuan, rising 9.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The tertiary industry registered a total output value of 1,362.
6 billion yuan over the first half of the year, up 8.1 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
