<HEADLINE> Development of China, Russia Benefits World: CPPCC Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The development of China and
Russia and their becoming strong are inevitable, and the Sino-
Russian friendly cooperation accords with the fundamental
interests of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the
remarks during a meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin.
</P>
<P>
Putin is on his first state visit to China after he assumed the
Russian presidency.
</P>
<P>
It is the common desire and in the fundamental interests of the
people of China and Russia for the two giant neighbors to
reinforce their friendly and cooperative relations, Li said.
</P>
<P>
And it's just a matter of time that both China and Russia will
become strong, and no force can block their development, Li stated.
</P>
<P>
"The development of China and Russia, their becoming strong,
the Sino-Russian friendly cooperation as well as their upholding
of justice together with the people the world over will be of
great significance to maintaining world peace and stability, to
the building of a just and fair new international order and to
pushing ahead the multi-polarization of the world," Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Russia are facing the same task of
domestic economic development and improving their people's living
standards. Internationally, the two countries share views on many
major issues. Therefore the two countries have a broad prospect
for further cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Putin praised CPPCC as having played an important role in China
's political life and in the establishment of a new international
political and economic order.
</P>
<P>
The president said Russia hopes to expand trade and enhance
exchanges and cooperation with China in all areas, citing the fact
that the exchanges between Russian parliament and China's CPPCC
has become an important component of the bilateral relations. And
such an exchange and cooperation will contribute to the long-term
friendly relations between the two countries in the new century.
</P>
