Norwegian peace brokers earlier this year to seek peace with the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels who are fighting
for a separate state in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983.
</P>
<P>
Moonesinghe's appointment to London comes at a time when Sri
Lanka is making a great effort in pressurizing the British
government to close down the LTTE office in London.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here believe that Moonesinghe, who is a good
negotiator, may be able to play an important role during his
tenure in London. 
