<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Court to Give Verdict on Anwar's Sodomy Trial Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The High Court here announced
Tuesday it will give on August 4 its verdict on the sodomy trial
of former deputy prime minister Anwar Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the date is tentative, Judge Arifin Jaka said "If I
am not ready, I will notify both parties. I will write my judgment
so that you all can look at it."
</P>
<P>
Arifin made the announcement after Anwar and Gobind Singh Deo,
counsel for Anwar's adopted brother Sukma Darmawan Sasmitaat Madja
finished their submissions at the end of the joint sodomy trial
Tuesday, the 117th day of the trial, one of the longest in the
Malaysian history.
</P>
<P>
The judge said he would base his decision solely on the
evidence before the court and for this he needs some time.
</P>
<P>
"As a Muslim, first I'm answerable to the next world. My
conscience is clear," Arifin told Anwar who personally replied to
points raised by the prosecution.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, 52, and Sukma, 39, are separately charged with
sodomizing Azizan Abu Bakar, 39, former driver of Anwar's family.
</P>
<P>
Sukma, a businessman, also faces another charge of abetting
Anwar to sodomize Azizan.
</P>
<P>
The prosecution closed its case against Anwar and Sukma on the
46th day of the trial on August 20 last year after calling nine
witnesses, including former inspector-general of police Haniff
Omar while the defence called 31 witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, also the former finance minister, is now serving a six-
year jail sentence for corrupt practices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
