<HEADLINE> Britain to Grant Swiss Citizens Border Privileges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Swiss President Adolf Ogi has
obtained guarantees from the British government that holders of
Swiss passports will soon be granted the same time-saving
privileges enjoyed by European Union (EU) nationals when entering
Britain.
</P>
<P>
British Prime Minister Tony Blair gave the assurance to Ogi on
Monday during their talks in London, said Swiss Radio
International.
</P>
<P>
Blair said that Britain would move as soon as possible to scrap
the need for Swiss citizens to join non-EU nationals for passport
control in often lengthy queues.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 600,000 Swiss citizens travel to Britain every
year, where about 500 Swiss companies are based.
</P>
<P>
Their discussions in London also focused on the progress being
made in the ratification of the bilateral treaties between the EU
and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Following their talks, Ogi said the British prime minister
would do all he could to ensure speedy ratification -- not just in
Britain but also in other EU states this year so that the
bilateral accords could come into effect on schedule in January.
</P>
</TEXT>
