<HEADLINE> Premier Zhu: China-Russia Trade Has Great Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that the Chinese government pays great attention to the
development of trade and economic cooperation with Russia and the
two sides should do more to explore the great potential.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks to Russian President Vladimir Putin, who
is on a state visit to China, his first since he won the
presidential election in March.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that although the two countries have witnessed growth
in trade and economic cooperation over the past several years,
enterprises of both China and Russia should increase contacts and
study each other's market to help expand trade and economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They can use economic means to push forward bilateral ties, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier also said he is looking forward to meeting
with Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Kasyanov for the fifth regular
meeting between prime ministers of the two countries later this
year in Beijing. He added that China is busy preparing for the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Putin said trade and economic cooperation between Russia and
China have bright prospects as the two countries are complementary
in their resources, technology, products and professionals.
</P>
<P>
He said the governments of the two countries should help
enterprises expand cooperation in various areas.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Kasyanov will bring home more firm cooperative
projects after his meeting with Zhu, Putin added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Chinese President Jiang Zemin exchanged views
with Putin on a wide range of issues. They also signed the Beijing
Declaration and a joint statement on the anti-ballistic missile
issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
