<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Killed, 20 Wounded in Ambush in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A military report reaching here said the ambush occurred at 6:
30 this morning in Matanog, Maguindanao, a few meters from the
headquarters of the 3rd Marine Battalion near the town hall.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, elements of the Army's 27th Infantry
Battalion were on their way to clear the area of rebels when they
were waylaid by about 100 MILF guerrillas who were waiting for the
convoy to pass.
</P>
<P>
The fighting came a day after a massacre in Lanao del Sur
province where suspected MILF secessionists shot dead 20 civilians
inside a mosque.
</P>
<P>
President Joseph Estrada ordered Tuesday the military and the
police to go after the perpetrators of the attacks.
</P>
<P>
Government officials said members of the MILF have split into
small group after their caps in Mindanao were overrun one after
another by government forces since April this year.
</P>
<P>
MILF Chairman Hashim Salamat called for a jihad against the
government after the falling of Camp Abubakar, the headquarters of
the MILF in Mindanao on July 9.
</P>
<P>
The 15,000-strong MILF has been fighting for an independent
Muslim State in Mindanao for more than two decades, a request
which has been repeatedly rejected by the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
