<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia's Foreign Trade Rises, Deficit Narrows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 18 (Xinhua) -- In the first half of this year,
Mongolian foreign trade amounted to 471.8 million U.S. dollars up
42.3 percent as compared with the same period last year, the
National Statistical Office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit dropped to 52.4 million dollars, 3.3 million
dollars lower than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
In the said period, exports amounted 209.7 million dollars and
imports 262.1 million dollars, up 52.1 percent and 35.4 percent
respectively from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Mineral products, textiles, raw and processed hides, skins
were the major export items. Vegetables, textiles, optical,
photographic and medical instruments were among the major import
items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
