<HEADLINE> Bierhoff to Remain Germany Captain: Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- AC Milan striker Oliver Bierhoff
was quoted by a German newspaper as saying on Tuesday that he
would remain the captain of Germany's national team.
</P>
<P>
"Head coach Rudi Voeller confirmed to me over the phone that I
would still be the captain," the 32-year-old Bierhoff told Bild
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
"I want to play for two more years and carry on until the (2002)
World Cup," he added. 
</P>
