<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Parrela Dropped from Olympic Team for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Sanderlei Parrela, Brazil's
silver medallist over 400 meters in the last world championships,
has been dropped from the country's Olympic team after failing a
dope test.
</P>
<P>
Parrela, 25, tested positive for steroid nandrolone during the
Brazilian Grand Prix meeting in May.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Athletics Confederation said Parrela was
suspended from all official competition until his case is heard by
the International Amateur Athletics Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
