<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Cooperation Enters New Phase: FM Spokesman (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia have ushered in a
new phase of bilateral cooperation, Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark here at a regular press conference in
response to a question about the ongoing visit by Russian
President Vladimir Putin to China.
</P>
<P>
This is Putin's first state visit to China as the Russian
president, and China attaches great importance to the trip, Zhu
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China had hoped the two countries would be able to
work together to draft the framework of the relationship between
the two countries. That goal has been fulfilled, the spokesman
said, as illustrated by the summit between Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Putin and the documents signed after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He told the press that the documents include the Beijing
declaration of China and Russia, and a joint statement of Chinese
and Russian presidents on the anti-ballistic missile issue Jiang
and Putin signed.
</P>
</TEXT>
