<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Cooperation with UK in Crackdown on Illegal Immigration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China is calling for cooperation
with Britain in fighting illegal immigration activities, said
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao at a regular press
conference this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhu was responding to a question on the recent death of 58
illegal Chinese immigrants in the English port of Dover.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said relevant Chinese departments are collecting blood
samples from family members of the dead, and the British police
are welcome to come to China once laboratory work on the blood
samples has been done.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the Chinese government wants to get support on the
matter from Britain and to cooperate with the British government
in investigating illegal immigration activities.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that both China and Britain, especially
Britain, will conduct careful investigations into the tragedy and
punish those persons responsible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
