<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in the Philippine
Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday as businessmen turned bearish
about the country's economic situation.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, declined 17.75
points to close at 1528.85. The broader all-shares index also
closed 6.46 points lower to 656.48.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 1.9 billion shares worth some 17.6 million U.
S.dollars on Tuesday against Monday's 1.2 billion shares worth
some 15.2 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday's trading, losers outnumbered winners 81 to 15,
while 42 shares unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investment confidence was affected by the
publication of a survey showing that the country's businessmen
have turned from cautiously optimistic in January to decidedly
bearish in June about the country's economic outlook. 
</P>
