<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda at High Risk of Polio Contraction: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has been listed among
African countries with a high risk of polio contraction after wild
polio cases are confirmed persisting in neighboring countries, the
New Vision daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's chances of being declared a polio-free state within
the next three years have diminished, said Dr. David Newberry of
Core International based in Atlanta, the United States.
</P>
<P>
This follows a recent report of a wild polio case in Pokot in
Kenya two weeks ago. Similar cases have been reported in Burundi
and the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), countries in the
same surveillance area as Uganda.
</P>
<P>
No country in the surveillance area can be declared polio-free
unless no polio case has been reported for six years, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to Newberry, Uganda is prone to wild polio attacks
mainly because of the insurgency in neighboring countries like the
DRC, Rwanda, Sudan and Somalia where people are forced to flee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
