<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Shakes Pakistan, Afghanista </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two persons were killed when a building collapsed in Peshawar,
the capital of Northwest Frontier Province. There was no immediate
report of casualty from other parts of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
According to the meteorological department of Pakistan, the
quake occurred at 3:54 a.m. Pakistan standard time (1054 GMT)and
the epicenter was located in the Kindukush range in Afghanistan,
some 200 kilometers north of Peshawar.
</P>
<P>
News reaching here said the quake was also felt in the Afghan
capital of Kabul but no report on casualties was immediately
available. 
