<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Samsung Develops 0.11 Micron Processing Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 18 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Samsung Electronics, a
semiconductor maker, announced Tuesday that it has developed 0.11
micron processing technology for 1Gb DRAM, the first one in the
world.
</P>
<P>
The thinnest one in the world so far was 0.12 micron processing
technology for 512Mb DRAM, which Samsung Electronics developed
last April.
</P>
<P>
Global semiconductor manufactures are competing to make circuit
width thinner for higher-density semiconductors.
</P>
<P>
Development of 0.11 micron processing technology for 1Gb DRAM
will advance the age of 1Gb DRAM by reducing funds necessary for
facility investments, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
