<HEADLINE> Putin on Russia's Security Cooperation With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Russian President
Vladimir Putin said here today that his country's cooperation with
China on international security can play a decisive role in world
peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Putin told reporters at a press conference after talks with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin this morning that the two countries
think alike on strengthening global balance, and this stance is
very important in today's world. He said Russia and China will
intensify the cooperation in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The two giant neighbors will expand their political and
economic cooperation, he said, adding that the package of
agreements signed today demonstrates that the two countries are
not only willing to, but also have begun to boost the cooperation
process.
</P>
<P>
The agreements cover the fields of power, energy, machinery and
aviation and aerospace.
</P>
<P>
Putin said he completely agreed to President Jiang's comment
during the morning talks that "neighbors are dearer than distant
relatives."
</P>
<P>
He said he is deeply convinced that the cooperation between the
two countries will be a success, because it is the common wish of
both the Russian and the Chinese people. 
</P>
