<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Strategic Partnership Benefiy Both </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Facts have proven that the Sino-
Russian strategic partnership of cooperation is not only in the
fundamental interests of the two countries and the two peoples,
but also beneficial to world peace and stability, said Chinese
President Jiang Zemin here today.
</P>
<P>
Such a new strategic partnership is non-aligned, non-
confrontational, and is not targeted toward any third party, Jiang
said in response to a question while meeting the press jointly
with President Vladimir Putin following their formal talks.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in recent years, the relationship between China
and Russia, two close neighbors and both permanent members of the
United Nations Security Council, has seen developing soundly.
</P>
<P>
With regard to bilateral ties, China and Russia will continue
to deepen their relationship and will become "good neighbors, good
partners and good friends," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
On the international stage, the two countries would continue to
devote themselves to the safeguarding of world peace and stability
and the establishment of a new political and economic world order,
</P>
<P>
To this end, Jiang noted the two countries would further expand
their cooperation in political, economic, military, and all other
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
