<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Presidents Sign Joint Statement on ABM Issue (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The statement says that political, legal and diplomatic means
must be used to strengthen international efforts in the matter,
prevent proliferation of weapons of mass destruction and their
carriers, explore possibilities for the setup of a global
monitoring system for preventing proliferation of missiles and
related technologies, and for carrying out extensive and non-
discriminative dialogue and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A non-strategic missile defense program and international
cooperation in such areas, which is not prohibited by ABM, should
not undermine security interests of other countries, not lead to
the establishment of any closed military or political bloc, or
threaten global and regional stability and security, it says.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia are deeply concerned that a certain country in
the Asia-Pacific region might deploy any such non-strategic
missile defense system, and steadfastly oppose this, it says. (
more)
</P>
</TEXT>
