</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000718.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Russia Presidents Sign Joint Statement on ABM Issue (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The damage wrought by ABM will trigger a new arms race and lead
to an about-face in the positive trend that appeared in world
politics after the end of the Cold War, the statement points out.
</P>
<P>
This is clearly not in the fundamental interests of any nation
in the world, it says, and the country that proposed an amendment
to ABM, a basic document in the area of disarmament, must "take
all responsibility" for undermining international stability and
security.
</P>
<P>
Analysis of the international situation shows that the demand
of a certain nation to amend ABM on the pretext of missile threat
is totally unjustified. The proposal to revise ABM is actually a
ruse to cover its attempt to violate ABM, it says.
</P>
<P>
The alteration of the content of ABM will harm the treaty and
lead to a chain of negative consequences, it says, noting that it
is of great immediate significance in the present strategic
situation to maintain the completeness and effectiveness of the
ABM treaty.
</P>
<P>
The statement says that the correct way to adapt oneself to the
new challenges in international security, safeguard world peace
and protect the legitimate security interests of different
countries is not to undermine ABM, but to push forward the
establishment of a just and rational international new political
order, abandon power politics and the random use of force in
international affairs, and strengthen regional and global security.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
