<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 24 points higher at 2,139 with a
turnover of 85.8 million NZ dollars (39.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight Telecom rallied 18 cents to 763 cents,
Independent News 20 to 400 cents, and pay television network Sky
TV 15 to 400 cents.
</P>
<P>
In the financial sector, AMP gained a further 5 cents to 2,205
cents, and Tower 1 cent to 521 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Building edged up 3 cents to 244 cents, while Fletcher
Energy fell 4 cents to 756 cents, and Fletcher Forests 2 to 84
cents.
</P>
<P>
Discount retailer the Warehouse rose 10 cents to 570 cents, and
Fletcher Paper closed unchanged at 247 cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
