<HEADLINE> American Glover Runs Year's Fastest Women's 400m hurdles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- American Sandra Glover ran the
fastest women's 400-meter hurdles of the year by clocking 53.33
seconds at the United States Olympic athletics trials in
Sacarmento, California, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
She beat world record holder Kim Batten to second. Batten, the
1996 Olympic silver medallist whose world record is 52.61 seconds,
registered a time of 54.70. Olympic bronze medallist Tonja Buford-
Bailey was third at 54.80 seconds. 
</P>
