<HEADLINE> Space Research Conference Opens in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 17 (Xinhua) -- An international conference on
space academic researches (COSPAR 2000) opened here Monday to
discuss issues including the establishment of Alfa orbit space
station and moon landing.
</P>
<P>
According to local TV reports, nearly 2,000 scientists from
more than 40 countries arrived for the meeting, co-chaired by
COSPAR president Gerald Haeren-Del and Polish organizing committee
chairman Janusz Ziellin-Ski.
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference will sum up the achievements and
activities done in the past century in space observation.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also exchange views on the latest
satellite observations regarding the surface of the Earth, the
oceans and the atmosphere, as well as space pollution.
</P>
<P>
Future space research activities will be another topic of the
conference. 
</P>
