<P>
No one was injured in the incident Monday morning, but
officials were concerned about the boy, who fled after the
shooting and remained at large hours later.
</P>
<P>
"We really want to find him before he does something else
stupid or something happens to him," said King County Sheriff's
Department spokesman John Urquhart.
</P>
<P>
He described the suspect as a white boy with dirty blonde hair
streaked with purple or blue. The boy was still believed to be
carrying a handgun, which apparently belonged to the boy's
grandmother, according to a TV report Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred at A.W. Dimmitt Middle School, where the
boy is among some 200 students enrolled for summer classes.
</P>
<P>
Urquhart said the boy walked into the cafeteria during a break
period before lunch, stood up on a table, shot once into the
ceiling and ordered all the students to get up on the cafeteria's
stage.
</P>
<P>
"At this point, students in the cafeteria -- and there was
quite a few of them -- went in pretty much all different
directions," Urquhart said.
</P>
<P>
When a teacher shouted to the boy that police were coming, he
ran, Brittany said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
