<HEADLINE> Hughes Reports Gain in Sales, Loss in Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Hughes Electronics Corp.
Monday reported a rise in sales but a loss in profit for the
second quarter, according to news release from the El Segundo,
California-based company.
</P>
<P>
Hughes said its sales rose to more than 1.8 billion dollars
from about 1.3 billion dollars in the same quarter a year ago,
while its net loss narrowed to 69 million dollars from 97 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hughes said its smaller loss was due primarily to a 76-million-
dollar charge taken in last year's second quarter at its satellite-
making business, which is being sold to Boeing.
</P>
<P>
Hughes posted a nearly 45-percent gain in second-quarter
earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization, to
179.6 million dollars from 124.3 million dollars
</P>
<P>
DirecTV, a satellite pay-TV service, was seeing subscriber
growth in urban and suburban markets after recently gaining the
ability to provide local TV channels, said Hughes Chairman
Michael Smith in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Hughes' satellite-TV units saw second-quarter sales rise to 1.2
billion dollars from 870 million dollars a year ago, but the group
had negative cash flow of 14 million dollars, vs. 11.5 million
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
At June 30, DirecTV had 8.7 million subscribers, including
about 435,000 from the Primestar service it acquired. 
</P>
