<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Formal Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
visiting Russian President Vladimir Putin held formal talks this
morning at the Great Hall of the People, following more than two
hours of private talks.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping in 1989
described his talks with the former Soviet Union leader as "the
end of the past and the beginning of the future."
</P>
<P>
At a time when the Sino-Russian relationship is poised to enter
the new century, Jiang said, his talk with Putin can be described
as "a pivotal conversation that inherits from the past and opens a
new chapter for the future."
</P>
<P>
Putin thanked Jiang for his invitation of him to China and for
the hospitable reception he received here. He told Jiang he was
delighted to spend a good time with friends in the friendly land
of China.
</P>
<P>
He stated that Russia attaches utmost importance to developing
the Russian-Chinese relations. He attributed the growth of the
well-grounded bilateral relationship to the unremitting efforts
made by Russia's first president Boris Yeltsin and President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Putin said his ongoing mission to China aims to consolidate the
existing good Russian-Chinese relationship and craft a blueprint
for long-term development of the ties.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that Jiang and Putin had conferred with
each other since Putin assumed the Russian presidency. The two
heads of state had their first meeting early this month when
attending the Shanghai Five Summit in Tajikistan's capital city
Dushanbe. 
</P>
