<HEADLINE> Soeharto to Be Tried Next Month : Attorney General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Attorney General
Marzuki Darusman insisted that former president Soeharto be
present in court when his corruption trial begins, possibly next
month.
</P>
<P>
"If Soeharto cannot attend the trial because of illness or
other factors, then the trial will have to be delayed until he can
appear in court," leading local newspapers Tuesday quoted Marzuki
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Lawyers for the former president earlier warned that their 79-
year-old client was physically unfit to stand trial, saying he has
deteriorating speech capability.
</P>
<P>
Marzuki has vowed to complete the dossier on the former tyrant
by August 10 with the trial expected soon afterward.
</P>
<P>
The team of prosecutors assigned to handle the case will soon
put the final touches on the dossier and the Attorney General
Office will write up the formal indictment next week, said Marzuki.
</P>
<P>
"We will make an announcement next week on the district court
selected to try the case, and the name of the prosecutor to handle
the case," he added.
</P>
<P>
With little cooperation from Soeharto, the investigating team
has built its case based on testimony from more than 100 people,
including his children and cronies and cabinet ministers who
served under him.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the State Development Audit Agency (BPKP) is now in
the
final stages of calculating the value of Soeharto's ill-gotten
wealth, Attorney General Office spokesman Yushar Yahaya said on
Monday, adding that the results are expected before the end of the
week.
</P>
<P>
He said the Attorney General Office has seized a number of
documents on Soeharto's accumulation of wealth, which reportedly
inflicted huge losses on the state during his 32 years in power.
</P>
<P>
He said the state prosecutors will soon seize more of Soeharto'
s assets, but he declined to name any properties or companies.
</P>
<P>
"They will be seized and held before the Soeharto files are
submitted to court," he added.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid has said Soeharto's wealth is about
45 billion U.S. dollars. The Time magazine last year put the
Soeharto clan's wealth at closer to 15 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
