<HEADLINE> Albania Becomes WTO Member </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Albania became a full member of the
World Trade Organization (WTO) on Tuesday, Ermelinda Meksi, the
minister of Economic Cooperation and Trade, announced.
</P>
<P>
He said that "the move will not only help the country to boost
its exports to other WTO members but also represents a giant step
toward signing an agreement on association with European Union (EU)
."
</P>
