<HEADLINE> Red-carpet Welcome for Putin (Details Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
hosted a red-carpet, 21-gun ceremony to welcome Russian President
Vladimir Putin at the plaza east to the Great Hall of the People
this morning.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state reviewed the guards of honor of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army after a military bank played the
national anthems of Russia and China.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the ceremony were Chinese Vice Premier
Qian Qichen, Vice-Chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee Jiang Chunyun, State Councilor and Defence
Minister Chi Haotian, Vice Chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Song Jian,
Vice Chairman of the Central Committee of China Democratic League
Lu Qiang, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, and Minister in charge of
the State Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan.
</P>
<P>
Putin's entourage, including Russian Deputy Prime Minister Ilya
Klebanov, Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov, Defense Minister Igor
Dmitriyevich Sergeyev, First Deputy Director of the Presidential
Office Dmitri Medvedev, Deputy Director of the Presidential Office
Sergei Prikhodko, Russian Ambassador to China Igor A. Rogachev,
Atomic Energy Minister Yevgeny Adamov and Power Minister Alexander
Gavrin, also attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Putin arrived in the Chinese capital Monday midnight for his
first state visit as guest of Jiang. 
</P>
