<HEADLINE> Portas Advances to Second Round in Croatian Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded Albert Portas from
Spain advanced to the second round of the 400,000 U.S. dollars
Croatian Open in Umag on Monday by beating Petr Kralert of the
Czech Republic 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Another Spaniard, two-time French Open champion Sergi Bruguera
had more trouble in defeating another Czech, Jiri Vanek. He
eventually advanced to the second round with a 6-3, 1-6, 7-5 win.
</P>
<P>
