<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Shareef Abdur-Rahim of the
Vancouver Grizzlies was added Monday to the U.S. Olympic
basketball team for the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
Abdur-Rahim replaces Grant Hill, who withdrew after breaking
his ankle during the NBA playoffs, and will join 11 other NBA
players on the team to be coached by Houston Rockets' Rudy
Tomjanovich.
</P>
<P>
In his fourth NBA season, Abdur-Rahim led Vancouver in scoring
with 20.3 points per game and rebounding at 10.1 per game.
</P>
<P>
His agent, Aaron Goodwin, said last week his client would be
picked for the team, which was confirmed by the USA Basketball's
announcement Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Team USA will begin training on August 26, in Maui, Hawaii,
and plays its first exhibition game on August 31, against the
Canadian national team at the University of Hawaii. 
