<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Works Hard to Advance in Stuttgart Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia made a heavy work of reaching the second round of the
Stuttgart Open with a hard-earned 7-6, 6-7, 7-6 victory over
little-known Frenchman Julien Boutter on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian, who has not played since losing to Sweden's Thomas
Johansson in the second round at Wimbledon, looked rusty against
an opponent ranked a modest 101st in the world.
</P>
<P>
The other two seeds in action on the opening day, Moroccans
Younes El Aynaoui and Karim Alami, also reached the second round.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed El Aynaoui beat wild card entrant Christian Vinck
of Germany 6-1, 7-6, while seventh seed Alami came back from a
disastrous start to move past Swede Fredrik Jonsson 0-6, 7-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
German Daniel Elsner delighted the home crowd by upsetting
Spanish baseliner Francisco Clavet 6-4, 4-6, 6-3. The 21-year-old
will play either top seed Magnus Norman or German Bjoern Phau.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia's Karol Kucera, twice a finalist in Stuttgart, cruised
into the second round by crushing Czech Slava Dosedel 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
</TEXT>
