<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebel FARC Announces Military Offensive to Be Kept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"This will continue until a ceasefire accord is made. That's
our organization's proposal at the negotiation table", said Ivan
Rios, guerrilla coordinator of subject-matter at the peace
process table.
</P>
<P>
FARC made last week attacks against 5 towns in Tolima and Huila
departments, west Colombia, in which 13 police, 5 guerrillas and 4
civilians were killed, and around 100 dwellings were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
High Commissioner for Peace, Camilo Gomez, expressed Tuesday
that only when the debate at the negotiation table is opened,
will it be possible to know the position of the parties which, for
now, remains in reserve.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, negotiators have already forwarded their stance.
The government wishes for a general ceasing of hostilities,
including kidnappings and extorsions which are some of the
guerrillas' main finance sources.
</P>
<P>
Colombian has been affected by a nearly four-decade long civil
war, which caused at least 35,000 dead in the last 10 years.
