<HEADLINE> Europe's Main Stock Markets Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Europe's main stock markets closed
lower Tuesday with technology and telecom stocks on the decline
and disappointing consumer price data from the U.S.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index of leading shares closed lower, dragged
down by telecom and bank shares and amid a weak start on Wall
Street. The index closed at 6,450.5 points, down 75 or 1.15
percent.
</P>
<P>
FTSE 100 heavyweight Vodafone AirTouch fell 3.7 percent and
cable telecom operator Colt Telecom dropped 3.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Financial data and media firm Reuters lost 3 percent, Internet
service provider Freeserve fell 4.5 percent and parent Dixons fell
4.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among other UK technology stocks, network equipment maker
Marconi fell 6.1 percent while information technology consulting
firm Logica lost 4.8 percent, shading several other significant
decliners.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 300 index fell 0.8 percent to 1,640.79. The
sub-indexes for information technology hardware and computer
software and services shed more than 3 percent each.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's Xetra Dax ended slightly lower with profit-taking
hitting tech stocks. The index ended at 7,406.91 points, down 23.
79 or 0.32 percent.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 in Paris was the weakest of the region's top bourses,
dropping 104.71 points, or 1.6 percent, to 6,514.54, with chip
maker STMicroelectronics being the biggest decliner, falling 6.2
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
