<HEADLINE> Eritrean Govt. Impedes Contacts Between POWs, Relatives: Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has claimed that
Eritrea is impeding communications between Eritrean prisoners of
war (POW) in Ethiopia and their relatives in Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Walta Information Center (WIC) Wednesday quoted Hagos Gemechu,
chief of the Tigray Branch of the Ethiopian Red Cross, as saying
that thousands of Eritrean POWs have written letters to their
relatives in Eritrea, but received no reply so far.
</P>
<P>
The POWs have stopped writing for fear that it might endanger
the safety of their loved ones, Hagos said. But he did not say
when the Eritrean soldiers were captured.
</P>
<P>
Hagos called on the International Committee of Red Cross to
exert pressure on the Eritrean government to allow communications
between the POWs and their relatives.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea signed a ceasefire agreement in mid-June
after a two-year border conflict. 
</P>
