<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Launches National Polio Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has launched an
emergency polio assessment all over the country with a view to
securing a certificate that proves the country is free from the
disease, the Health Ministry announced here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A rapid and continuous vaccination program will be undertaken
in those areas identified in the assessment as not free from polio,
the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
About 280 children in Ethiopia die of polio every year, the
ministry said, adding some parents hide their polio victim
children due to superstitious beliefs.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, Ethiopia is one of the 14 African
and Southeast Asian countries where polio is believed to be rife.
</P>
<P>
Appealing to the public at large to exert utmost efforts to
kick polio out the country, the Ethiopian Health Ministry urged
parents to take their children to health centers as soon as they
contract the virus that causes polio. 
</P>
