four years since the foundation of the organization in 1996, it "
is now fully involved", Guterres added.
</P>
<P>
The summit unanimously chose Dulce Pereira, an official of the
Brazilian Culture Ministry, as its new executive secretary and set
its next summit for Brazil in 2002. The CPLP, whose member
countries span three continents, also emerged strengthened from
the summit through decisions to create CPLP institutions in all
the member states, Guterres stressed.
