<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Lifts Fish Ban on Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has lifted its
ban on Uganda's fish exports, the New Vision daily reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Fisheries Minister Fred Mukisa was quoted as saying
that he had got a parcel from Brussels that the ban on Uganda fish
was lifted on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the minister said he is yet to receive an official
declaration although he is sure of his sources.
</P>
<P>
"They (EU) are likely to send the official statement in two or
three weeks' time after which we shall send them a list of our
approved processing plants and start exporting on bilateral terms,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral status means that Uganda will export fish to EU
countries with which it has independent arrangement.
</P>
<P>
The ban, which affected the whole East African region due to
massive fish poisoning in Lake Victoria, took effect in Uganda on
April 14, 1999 and has since cost the country 30 million U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
